title: 2012 Jobing.com Women's Cycling Clinic
description: Women\'s Cycling Clinic. The goal of the clinic is to become more comfortable and self-sufficient on the bike and give women the opportunity to meet and ride with other women in a non-competitive atmosphere.
course: Open to Beginner/Intermediate riders, all participants will benefit from the sessions which have been developed to teach the basics as well as more advanced information regarding the most important aspects of cycling. Sessions provide classroom instruction on key concepts such as nutrition and basic maintenance as well as practical application of important cycling concepts such as stretching and core conditioning to improve overall cycling fitness.

5th Annual Bike the Bluff Citizen's Ride
description: Bike the Bluff Omnium is a 2 day stage race that consists of a road race, citizen\'s fun ride and Criterium.  The race is held in Show Low, Arizona and is surrounded by the beautiful White Mountains.  This is the 5th Annual Bike the Bluff and proceeds benefit the 501C (3) non-profit organization, Mountain Christian School and Two-wheel Jones Racing.
course: The fun ride for the citizen\'s will be a 55 mile road course
directions:
From Phoenix- Take the SR 87 to US 260 (East, to Heber/Overguard) to the 60 (East Deuces of Clubs Rd), then north on 180 about 1 block make a left on Thorton Rd
From Mesa- Take the US 60 through Globe and continue on the US 60 all the way to Show Low.  Go past victorian house on the US 60 until 77.  Make a right and continue to for 1 block then make a left onto Thorton Rd.

title: Sabino Cycles 4TH OF JULY FREEDOM RIDE
Single Track Bike Shop Road Race
TOUR DE SUMMIT
description: Come and tour the White Mountains of Northern Arizona! White Mountain Endurance Sports and Summit Healthcare have teamed up to bring you an exciting, high-elevation ride through some of the most beautiful parts of Arizona. Please visit our website at www.wmendurance.com for more detailed information.
course: The Tour de Summit will begin on July 14, 2012 at 6:30 AM from historic downtown Snowflake, Arizona.  The race will include three different routes that participants can register for: 80 mile, 56 mile, and a 22 mile courses. All three courses will end at the same finish point in Snowflake, Arizona. Please visit our website at www.wmendurance.com for more detailed course information, inlcuding maps and elevations for each of the three routes.
registration: Registration can be completed online at www.active.com/triathlon/snowflake-az/tour-de-summit-2012.  Registration will close on Thursday July 12, 2012 at 11:59 PM PST.
notes: Please visit our website at www.wmendurance.com for more detailed information.
directions: Finally!!! An opportunity for cyclists to escape the mid-summer heat to a cool, mountainous, race through the pines and high desert plains. Located just 2.5 hours North of Phoenix, the towns of Snowflake and Taylor, Arizona offer the perfect escape. Whether your a competetive athlete looking for a challenge, or a recreational cyclist, we\'ve got what you\'re looking for. Come enjoy the 1st annual Tour de Summit! Please visit our website at www.wmendurance.com for more detailed information.

title: The Ride430 Challenge 2012
description: The Ride 430 Challenge is a charity bicycle ride that begins in Scottsdale Arizona and ends 3 1/2 days later in San Diego, California.  The mission of the Ride430 Challenge is to raise funds and awareness for the needs of our injured heroes.
course: The coarse is a map drawn by the team that begins in Scottsdale and ends in San Diego.

title: Business Builder
description: Think of this ride as business networking on your bike. Some people do business on the golf course...we love to ride our mountain bikes and know there are other business professional like us.
course: Ride start and finish at Sweetwater Trail head.  Social no drop group ride.  There is a smaller fast group ride option.  Duration 60 to 90 minutes followed by post ride social.  Please be respectful and ride on established trails.
registration: Registration from 4pm to 4:30pm at the Trail Head parking lot
directions: Exit west from I-10 on Camino Del Cerro. West to Tortollita Rd. South on Tortollita Rd until the end, trail head is at the end of Tortollita Td.

title: FASTER Gran Fondo
description: The inaugural FASTER Gran Fondo brings cyclists together for a weekend of riding, cycling related festivities and special celebrity guests.  FASTERs Gran Fondo is not a bike race, but a challenging and supported bike ride. Cyclists will depart Scottsdale, AZ and complete 50 or 100 mile distances.
course: The supported ride will go through the scenic cities of Scottsdale, Cave Creek, and Fountain Hills and will have an electronic chip-timed King and Queen of the mountain award.  The 50 mile riders will have an opportunity to beat the clock on Cave Creek Road just east of Lone Mountain and upward to a point between Bartlett Lake Road and Old Mine Road.  There will be a single male and female winner in the 50 mile event recognized in the post-race ceremonies.  The 100 mile riders will have the opportunity to compete in two climb categories:  individually on the challenging Golden Eagle Boulevard in Fountain Hills, and a combined time from the climb on Cave Creek Road early and the Golden Eagle climb later in the 100 mile ride.  1st place male and female will be awarded for the fastest Golden Eagle time, as well as who is the fastest on the combined time from both climbs

title: 12 & 24 Hours of Fury
description: In partnership with Trek Bikes, Muscle Milk and McDowell Mountain Regional Park, 4 Peaks Racing is proud to bring you the Valley of the Suns premier endurance mountain bike event - The 12 & 24 Hours of Fury! This event challenges participants to complete loops around the perimeter of one of Arizonas most popular courses: the Competitive Track at McDowell Mountain Regional Park. The only rule is a simple one - the most loops in 12 or 24 hours wins all the glory!
course: Competitive Track at McDowell Mountain Regional Park
